Has anybody heard of Neways?  www.neways.com

I've been in contact with them recently with regards to an employment possiblity - becoming one  of their national distributors.  People have made millions from it - working on a similar concept to Avon (the wonderful cosmetics company), or (a little more similarly) Amway, the (margianlly nicer) cleaning products people.  The chap on the 'phone said it wasn't at all to do with sales, but the informative DVD he sent me didn't give that impression AT all!!!

I'm intruiged - how can you make money from profit on products that you've convinced people to buy, and it not be selling?!  The other way people make money is by building a vast "organisation," network of distributors that yuo've recruited, and that other people have recruited - and you get commission from THEIr sales.  SO, for example - if i recruit 2 people, and each of those recruit 5, i recieve the commission from 12 representatives - and so on.  But it's still convincing people to "buy" a job.  Or relying on people being passed my name.  And the other thing!  i live in Parkstone!  grotty place where people would sooner swallow bleach than spend lots of money on additive free products!

For those of you who have not yet awoken, BB7 started 5 days ago.  And it's going surprisingly well, from the hosuemates' point of view - they all love each other, get on well, and Big Brother's attempts at dividing them is bringing them together; they're working together well, sharing, and supporting each other.

With the exception of possibly the most annoying man in the WORLD.  No, I lie.  He's worse than annoying.  He sepent this evening saying he wanted to go back to his own little world, back to his council house, where he spent his time in solitary confinement becuase he didnt' have any friends.  And watching thew ay he behaved just now, is it any WONDER?!  He realy upset Lisa, by calling her an imbecile (because the rest of the group didn't stop what they were doing to look at him while he was reading slowly, letter by letter).  But anyway, they decided that as he'd upset everyone so much they were going to discount himf rom the group, which I think is understandable.  And in payback, he went and took ALL the foodstuffs, and chucked them in a box in the garden.  Yeh - becuase that's going to make htem like you isn't it, you fucking cunt?!

he calls himself a "paki poof," and blames his behaviour on that.  As Dawn pointed out to him, that's no excuse for his beahviour.  I think she tookt he wrong approach though, instead of talking to him as an equal, she needed to talk down to him, like a child.  As he does with the rest of the group.  the way he talks to the ret of the group shows that he's still mentally got the maturity of a 6 year old. ANYWAY, I know other "paki poofs," as he describes them, who behave impeccabley.  i've seen better behaved creatures at the ZOO.  Now, for my suggestion.

I reckon, if we (the We-Hate-Shabhaz-Gruop, and i'm sure it's oigng to be HUGE) all put in a couple of quid, we should have enough to hire a helicopter.  We hover over the BB hosue in it, and when SHabhaz comes into the garden, we SHOOT him with a rifle.  Not a pussy air-rifle, but a proper heavy duty one like you'd use to kill a rhino or some other more intelligent beast.

Who's with me?!

Wow!  Once again, pointless web browsing has prompted me to post ramblinbs.  But fab ones!

http://www.familyfriendlychurches.org.uk/midihymns/HP352.MID

See if you can pick out the well known, seasoonal (although it's out of season atm,) hymn tune.  These are backing tracks for people to use in church.  Now i hate "happy clappy" hymns, and music groups drive me insane (i think it's the mix of 3 8 year old violinists, the old lady at the piano, the flute player, the little boy on the drum kit sounding over everybody else, the sunday shcool with their tambourines, etc.) But THIS, traditional hymns done liek this?  I love it!  mind you, i have a hting for heavy electronica (my CD collection of things like erasure, client, pet shop boys says it all really)

http://www.familyfriendlychurches.org.uk/midihymns/HP452.MID
http://www.familyfriendlychurches.org.uk/midihymns/HP528.MID
http://www.familyfriendlychurches.org.uk/midihymns/HP409.MID


Blessed assurance sounds decidedly parisienne.  And there's this yapping dog sample they keep using (i think it's part of percussion set, supposed to sound like deck scratching or whatever it is they call it).

And i'll leave you with this, i just liked the name of the tune: http://www.familyfriendlychurches.org.uk/midihymns/HP722.MID - ARMAGEDDON

I can't remember what the tunes are now, but i know one of them was aberystwyth, one was great is we plough the fields, and i can't remember the third!  But anyway!  Enjoy.  this is what hymns should be like!

I have just had the most amusing hour Ever.  Slightly sad, I know, but.  I found a website on Baragami (the welsh art of toast arranging, http://www.messybeast.com/baragami/baragami.htm)

The toast arranging is silly, but there's some interesting suggestions, including a man who did mosaics (good photo of Dame Edna depicted forever in burnt toast), and the notion of a toasteddfod (get it, eisteddfod?  nope just me that was both amused and intrigued).

On this site, i found one to http://www.poppadom.org.uk/, which stands for People Out Practising Paperfolding And Dining On Masala.  Including some AWFUL (yet strangely amusing) renames of our favourite songs: Poppadom Preach (Madonna, Korma Chameleon (Culture Club), Poppas got a brand now Saag (James Brown), You Can't Curry Love (Supremes), It's My Chapati and I Cry If I Want To (Dave Stewart and Barbara Gaskin), Dansak on the Ceiling (Lionel Richie), We Are Jalfrezi (Sister Sledge).  I could go on, but I feel you might throw things at me.  Pun(jab) central, i thought.  I'll leave you with some ABBA: Tikka chance on me, Wateralloo / Vindallo, Dansak Queen, The winner takes a dahl, Chicken Tikka (you and I know).

http://www.nickrobinson.info/clients/poppadom/queen.htm are some alternative lyrics to a well known Queen song: I See a Little Chicken Tikka on the Side; Rogan Josh, Rogan Josh, Pass the Chutney Made of Mango; Vindaloo Does Nicely - Very Very Spicy - see if you can guess the song!!!

Basically, lots of laughter to be had.  If anybody comes up with anythign to match, share it!!!

ANd before I leave you, YES!  I do have too much time on my hands :P
